Access Bank of Nigeria Says First-Half Profit Increased 15%

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-08-17T17:04:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/access-bank-of-nigeria-says-first-half-profit-increased-15-1-.html
  Access Bank Plc (ACCESS) , a Nigerian lender,
said its operating profit for the six months to June 30
increased 15 percent to 15.5 billion naira ($100.7 million).  Profit before tax rose 6.1 percent to 10.4 billion naira,
the Lagos-based lender said in an e-mailed statement today.
Access will pay a dividend of 20 kobo per share for the period,
it said.  Access shares gained 23 kobo, or 3.8 percent, to 6.28
naira, by the 2:30 p.m. close in Lagos, its highest since Aug.
5. The stock has declined 34 percent this year, compared with a
7.9 percent fall in the Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index
over the same period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
